15179 /******************************************************************************/
15180 /* For a painless codes migration between the STM32F3xx device product */
15181 /* lines, the aliases defined below are put in place to overcome the */
15182 /* differences in the interrupt handlers and IRQn definitions. */
15183 /* No need to update developed interrupt code when moving across */
15184 /* product lines within the same STM32F3 Family */
15185 /******************************************************************************/
15186 
15187 /* Aliases for __IRQn */
15188 #define ADC1_IRQn ADC1_2_IRQn
15189 #define SDADC1_IRQn ADC4_IRQn
15190 #define COMP1_2_IRQn COMP1_2_3_IRQn
15191 #define COMP2_IRQn COMP1_2_3_IRQn
15192 #define COMP_IRQn COMP1_2_3_IRQn
15193 #define COMP4_6_IRQn COMP4_5_6_IRQn
15194 #define HRTIM1_FLT_IRQn I2C3_ER_IRQn
15195 #define HRTIM1_TIME_IRQn I2C3_EV_IRQn
15196 #define TIM15_IRQn TIM1_BRK_TIM15_IRQn
15197 #define TIM18_DAC2_IRQn TIM1_CC_IRQn
15198 #define TIM17_IRQn TIM1_TRG_COM_TIM17_IRQn
15199 #define TIM16_IRQn TIM1_UP_TIM16_IRQn
15200 #define TIM19_IRQn TIM20_UP_IRQn
